# Bun-Only Package Management

Use Bun for all dependency management and script execution in this project.

## Required

- Use `bun install` instead of `npm install`.
- Use `bun add <pkg>` / `bun add -d <pkg>` for dependencies.
- Use `bun remove <pkg>` to remove dependencies.
- Use `bun run <script>` to run scripts from `package.json`.
- Use `bun x <tool>` for one-off CLIs.

## Avoid

- Do not use `npm`, `npx`, `npm ci`, or `npm run`.
- Do not suggest npm commands in docs, examples, or PR notes.

## Examples

```bash
# ❌ Bad
npm install
npm run lint
npx eslint .

# ✅ Good
bun install
bun run lint
bun x eslint .
```
